(41, 6, 29, 11, 13, 29, 30, 'took up his corpse, and laid it', 'Burial and Mourning Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of taking up a corpse and laying it to rest, highlighting the themes of mourning and burial. The disciples in Mark and the prophet in 1 Kings both show reverence for the deceased.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 29, 40, 27, 57, 60, 'laid it in a tomb', 'Burial of the Body', 'Both passages emphasize the act of taking and laying the body in a tomb. This connection highlights the significance of burial in the narrative of death.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 29, 44, 8, 2, 2, 'laid it in a tomb', 'Burial and Lamentation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of burial and the mourning that follows. In Mark, the disciples lay the corpse in a tomb, while in Acts, devout men carry Stephen to his burial and lament over him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 42, 9, 10, 10, NULL, 'Apostles'' Report to Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the apostles'' return and their report to Jesus about their activities. This connection highlights the shared theme of communication and reflection between the apostles and Jesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 42, 10, 17, 17, NULL, 'Return of the Disciples', 'This connection highlights the theme of the apostles returning to Jesus to report their experiences. Both passages emphasize the joy and authority the disciples felt after their missions, showcasing their successes in teaching and casting out devils.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 40, 10, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Apostolic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the apostles. Mark 6:30 mentions the apostles gathering to report their activities, while Matthew 10:2 lists their names, establishing their identity and mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 44, 20, 18, 21, 'what they had done, and what they had taught', 'Teaching and Testifying Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of teaching and sharing experiences. In Mark, the apostles recount what they had done and taught, while in Acts, Paul reflects on how he taught publicly and from house to house.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 56, 2, 6, 7, 'what they had done, and what they had taught', 'Exhortation and Good Works', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing experiences and teaching. In Mark, the apostles recount their actions, while Titus encourages showing a pattern of good works. This connection highlights the role of communication and integrity in ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 41, 6, 7, 13, 'what they had done, and what they had taught', 'Apostolic Mission and Reporting', 'Both passages emphasize the apostles'' mission and their actions. The first passage describes their sending forth and activities, while the second highlights their return to report on what they had done and taught.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 30, 44, 1, 1, 2, 'what they had done, and what they had taught', 'Connection of Apostolic Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the apostles'' role in sharing what they had done and taught. Mark highlights the apostles reporting to Jesus, while Acts references Jesus beginning to do and teach through the apostles.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 31, 41, 3, 20, 20, NULL, 'Theme of Lack of Leisure', 'Both passages emphasize the inability to eat due to overwhelming crowds. In Mark 3:20, the multitude''s presence prevents eating, while Mark 6:31 highlights the need for rest because of constant demands.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 31, 43, 6, 1, 1, 'Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place', 'Rest and Movement of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus leading his disciples away for rest, as seen in Mark 6:31, and then moving to a new location in John 6:1. Both passages emphasize the activity of Jesus amidst the demands of the crowd.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 31, 41, 1, 45, 45, 'desert place', 'Desert Places and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of desert places where Jesus and his followers find themselves. In Mark 6:31, Jesus invites his disciples to rest in a desert place, while in Mark 1:45, Jesus is found in desert places due to the crowds seeking him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 31, 41, 3, 7, 7, 'Come ye yourselves apart', 'Withdrawal for Rest', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' withdrawal with his disciples to escape the crowds. In Mark 6:31, Jesus invites them to rest, while in Mark 3:7, he also withdraws to the sea amidst a multitude. This connection highlights the theme of seeking solitude amid busyness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 31, 40, 14, 13, 13, 'desert place', 'Desert Place and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of retreating to a ''desert place'' for rest. This connection highlights Jesus'' intention to find solitude amidst the demands of the crowd.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 32, 41, 4, 36, 36, 'departed into a desert place by ship', 'Departure to a Desert Place', 'Both passages emphasize the act of departing by ship. In Mark 6:32, the disciples leave for a desert place, while Mark 4:36 describes them taking Jesus in the ship after sending away the multitude.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 32, 41, 6, 45, 45, 'into a desert place by ship', 'Disciples'' Journey by Ship', 'Both passages emphasize the act of departing by ship. The first verse describes the disciples leaving to a desert place, while the second verse mentions them getting into the ship to go to the other side.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 32, 40, 14, 13, 21, 'desert place', 'Desert Place Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the ''desert place'' where Jesus and his disciples went. This setting serves as the backdrop for the miraculous feeding of the multitude, highlighting the need for sustenance in a remote area.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 32, 43, 6, 5, 13, 'desert place', 'Feeding the Multitude Connection', 'This connection highlights the transition from Jesus and his disciples seeking solitude in a ''desert place'' to the miraculous feeding of a large crowd. Both passages emphasize the need for sustenance and the miraculous provision of food in a remote setting.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 32, 42, 9, 10, 17, 'desert place', 'Desert Place Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of retreating to a ''desert place'' for rest and reflection. This connection highlights the apostles'' need for solitude after their ministry efforts, which leads to the miraculous feeding of the multitude.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 33, 43, 6, 2, 2, NULL, 'Crowds Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the large crowds that followed Jesus, motivated by their knowledge of his miracles and teachings. The people in Mark ran to him, while in John, a multitude followed because of the miracles he performed.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 33, 40, 15, 29, 31, 'came together unto him', 'Healing and Gathering of Crowds', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of large crowds around Jesus, who is recognized and sought after for healing. The people in Mark 6:33 ''came together unto him,'' paralleling the multitude in Matthew 15:29-31 who brought the sick to Jesus for healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 33, 41, 6, 54, 55, 'knew him, and ran', 'Crowds Recognizing Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the people''s recognition of Jesus and their eagerness to seek him out. In each instance, the crowds run to him, demonstrating their urgency and desperation for healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 33, 59, 1, 19, 19, NULL, 'Listening and Response', 'This connection highlights the importance of being attentive and responsive. In Mark, the people are swift to gather and hear Jesus, while James encourages being ''swift to hear'' in communication.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 34, 40, 9, 36, 36, 'sheep not having a shepherd', 'Compassion for the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the people, describing them as ''sheep not having a shepherd.'' This connection highlights the shared imagery of the crowds being lost and in need of guidance.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 34, 4, 27, 17, 17, 'sheep not having a shepherd', 'Shepherd Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the need for leadership among the people, depicting them as ''sheep'' without a shepherd. This connection highlights the importance of guidance and care in the community.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 34, 42, 9, 11, 11, 'moved with compassion toward them', 'Compassion and Healing Connection', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' compassion for the people, as both passages describe him responding to their needs. In Mark, he is moved with compassion and teaches, while in Luke, he receives them and heals those in need.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 34, 14, 18, 16, 16, 'sheep not having a shepherd', 'Sheep Without a Shepherd', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of people as sheep without a shepherd, highlighting their need for guidance and care. This connection illustrates a shared theme of compassion and concern for the lost.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
