(41, 6, 34, 58, 4, 15, 15, 'moved with compassion toward them', 'Compassion and Infirmities Connection', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' compassion for the people as he sees them as sheep without a shepherd, paralleling the high priest''s understanding of human infirmities. Both passages emphasize a deep empathy and shared experience of suffering.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
